  "description": {
   "en": "It was the Sengoku Era, a time when warring Daimyō usurped each other constantly.   \nThere was a man whose soul was overtaken by the ways of tea and material greed \nas he strenuously worked his way up towards greater power and status.   \nHis name was Furuta Sasuke, a vassal of Oda Nobunaga in the Yamashiro province.   \nWith his world broadened by Oda's genius and Tea Master Sen no Sōeki's spiritual insight, \nSasuke travelled the road of the Hyouge Mono or \"comical fellow\".   \nTo live or not to live. For power or the arts. \nThat is the question!  \n  \n---\n- **2009 Japan Media Arts Festival Excellence Prize winner**\n- **2010   14th Osamu Tezuka Cultural Grand Prize Award winner**"
  },
